latestPosts.caption:
The past six months have been anything but easy. After completing my master’s, I transitioned into full-time work—and that shift made me realise how inactive I’ve become, both on social media and in real life.

Balancing life isn’t as simple as it sounds. Each night, I go to bed thinking about the 9-to-5 routine ahead, and by 5 PM, I’m already drained, just wanting to go home and rest.

But lately, I’ve started to accept this new phase and remind myself: work hard, not just for the job—but for yourself ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
Never give up on your dreams. Believe me, back in 2022, I came in with a heartbreak, no friends, no family but today I’ve my own family, friends, house and a job; clearly cutting down ties with clown people and their masked faces: But all in all, learnt a lot in this topsy turvy ride away from home.
For everyone out there, always be brave and determined, stand out in your own decisions with your own handful of people because it’s your life after all, and you’ll see that you made the right decisions all over :))
Thank you mummy papa for everything 🧿
